assertionDisputedCallback(bytes32).custom:security: Automatic deletion only occurs when msg.sender is the Optimistic Oracle V3
assertionDisputedCallback(bytes32).details: If called by Optimistic Oracle V3, the disputed proposal is auto-deleted. If called by any      other address, this attempts upgrade-safe cleanup via deleteProposalOnUpgrade and will revert      unless an Optimistic Oracle V3 upgrade has been detected.

params.assertionId: The ID of the disputed assertion

assertionResolvedCallback(bytes32,bool).custom:security: Only callable by the Optimistic Oracle V3 contract
assertionResolvedCallback(bytes32,bool).details: Updates lastFinalizedTimestamp if assertion resolved truthfully

params.assertedTruthfully: Whether the bundle data was validated as truthful
params.assertionId: The ID of the resolved assertion

constructor.details: Calls setUp with encoded parameters for proxy compatibility

params._bondAmount: Base bond amount for bundle proposals
params._collateral: Address of the collateral ERC20 token
params._finder: Address of the UMA Finder contract

deleteProposalOnUpgrade(bytes32).custom:security: Reentrancy protected, validates oracle upgrade detection
deleteProposalOnUpgrade(bytes32).details: Detects oracle upgrades and removes proposals to allow re-proposal

params.proposalHash: The hash of the proposal to delete

getCurrentTime().custom:testing: Can be overridden for testing different time scenarios
getCurrentTime().details: Virtual function to allow overriding in tests

getProposalBond().details: Returns the maximum of configured bondAmount and oracle minimum bond

returns._0: The required bond amount in collateral token units

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proposeBundle(string).custom:events: Emits BundleProposed with timestamp and proposer details
proposeBundle(string).custom:security: Requires the proposer to approve at least `bondAmount` collateral for this contract.                  The oracle enforces a minimum bond; if `bondAmount` is below the minimum, the                  assertion will revert unless configuration is adjusted accordingly.
proposeBundle(string).details: Creates an assertion for bundle data validity at current timestamp. The claim asserted to      the Optimistic Oracle V3 is the raw `_bundleData` bytes (no additional keys/rules encoding). Process: 1. Stores bundle data with timestamp and proposer 2. Creates optimistic assertion for data validity 3. Tracks assertion for later resolution

params._bundleData: String representation of bundle data to be validated

proposeTransactions((address,uint8,uint2.custom:events: Emits TransactionsProposed with full proposal details
proposeTransactions((address,uint8,uint2.custom:security: Reentrancy protected, validates all transaction parameters
proposeTransactions((address,uint8,uint2.details: Creates an assertion at the Optimistic Oracle V3 with bonded collateral Requirements: - Transactions must target valid addresses (not zero address) - If a transaction includes calldata, the `to` address must be a contract - Proposer must have approved sufficient collateral - Proposal must not be a duplicate Security considerations: - Validates transaction targets to prevent invalid proposals - Bonds collateral to ensure proposer commitment - Stores proposal hash for later execution verification

params.explanation: Optional explanation of the proposal's intent and rationale
params.transactions: Array of transactions to be executed if proposal succeeds

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setCollateralAndBond(address,uint256).details: Collateral token must be whitelisted by UMA governance

params._bondAmount: The base bond amount required for proposals
params._collateral: The ERC20 token to use as collateral

setEscalationManager(address).custom:security: Only callable by contract owner, validates contract existence
setEscalationManager(address).details: Can be set to zero address to disable escalation management

setIdentifier(bytes32).details: Identifier must be supported by UMA's identifier whitelist

params._identifier: The new identifier for validating proposals

setLiveness(uint64).custom:security: Only callable by contract owner, validates reasonable bounds
setLiveness(uint64).details: Must be greater than 0 and less than 5200 weeks (maximum allowed)

setRules(string).details: Rules string cannot be empty and is used in claim construction

setUp(bytes).details: Decodes and sets up collateral, rules, identifier, and liveness

sync().details: Updates Optimistic Oracle V3 address if it has changed in the Finder

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
